requirement_issues.requirement_text: System shall operate on a system capable of multi-processing.

issues.description: The term 'system' is used twice and it is unclear whether this refers to the application, the hardware platform, or both. 'Multi-processing' is undefined (e.g., number and type of cores).
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify that the Smart-Home application shall run on a hardware platform supporting symmetric multi-processing with at least N physical or logical cores.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: System shall operate on a system capable of near-real time execution of instructions.

issues.description: 'Near-real time' is vague with no specific latency or determinism parameters, making it unclear what qualifies as near-real time.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify a maximum end-to-end latency (e.g., 'The system shall guarantee instruction execution within 10 ms under normal load conditions').

requirement_issues.requirement_text: System shall have a database associated with it that can handle transaction processing at a rate of 1000 transactions per minute.

issues.description: This requirement specifies a fixed rate of 1000 transactions per minute, but the Database class has a configurable 'transactionRatePerMinute' attribute, causing conflict between fixed and configurable specifications.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify whether 1000 transactions per minute is a minimum or default value, or adjust the requirement to refer to the configurable attribute appropriately.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: If system supports recording more than three television shows simultaneously, then system shall have separate video recorder.

issues.description: This requirement references 'more than three' shows, but another requirement specifies support for only two simultaneous recordings, creating inconsistency in recording capacity thresholds.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify the exact threshold for when a separate video recorder is required and ensure consistency across related requirements.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: SH system shall be usable by those with slight eye loss.

issues.description: No guidance on what 'usable' means for users with visual impairment or required accessibility features (e.g., font size, contrast, screen reader support).
issues.suggested_fix: Define specific accessibility criteria (e.g., support 16pt minimum font, high-contrast color schemes, WCAG 2.1 AA screen-reader compatibility).

issues.description: 'Usable by those with slight eye loss' is not measurable or testable as stated, lacking acceptance criteria.
issues.suggested_fix: Introduce measurable acceptance criteria, such as user testing with a standard vision acuity threshold or compliance with an accessibility standard.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: System shall be easy to use.

issues.description: The term 'easy to use' is subjective, unmeasurable, and untestable without defined usability metrics or acceptance criteria.
issues.suggested_fix: Define specific, measurable usability criteria such as task completion time, error rate, satisfaction scores from user surveys, or maximum clicks/steps for common tasks, referencing established usability testing protocols.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: System shall be understood by users of all levels of understanding with no more than 4 hours of training.

issues.description: The requirement does not define 'users of all levels of understanding' or what constitutes 'understanding the system', making it impractical to test.
issues.suggested_fix: Define specific user categories (e.g., beginner, intermediate, advanced) and measurable understanding criteria (e.g., ability to complete X tasks independently after training).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: System shall trigger warning and require additional confirmation when users select levels outside of the manufacturer's settings for dangerous levels of smoke and carbon dioxide.

issues.description: The form of 'additional confirmation' is unclear (modal dialog, audible alert, second button press) and the actor for confirmation is unspecified.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the UI behavior and confirmation mechanism, for example: 'The system shall display a modal dialog requiring the user to click Confirm before accepting thresholds outside manufacturer limits.'

requirement_issues.requirement_text: System shall accept desired temperature settings for each zone, for no less than four periods in the day.

issues.description: The term 'period' is undefined: it is unclear whether periods are fixed intervals or user-defined, and how they should be represented.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify that a 'period' is a user-configurable time interval with explicit start and end times, and that at least four distinct intervals must be supported per 24-hour cycle.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: System shall accept definitions for the range for time-of-day savings.

issues.description: The term 'range for time-of-day savings' is unclear, with no specification of type (time periods, percentage savings) or definition format.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify whether this refers to time ranges when savings rates apply, percentage ranges for savings, or other range definitions.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: System may skip commercials when system is able to detect the commercial.

issues.description: The requirement doesn't specify how commercials are detected, acceptable detection methods, or accuracy requirements.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify commercial detection methods (e.g., audio signatures, time-based, metadata-based) and minimum accuracy thresholds.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Coffee maker shall stop within 1 microsecond when button is pressed.

issues.description: A 1 microsecond response time is technically infeasible for a physical coffee maker system.
issues.suggested_fix: Change to a realistic timeframe such as 100 milliseconds or 1 second to ensure immediate user-perceived response.

missing_requirements.description: Secure user authentication, account management, and session management features are missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall provide secure user authentication with unique accounts for each household member; support password and biometric authentication; require multi-factor authentication for all remote access; allow administrators to create, modify, and delete user accounts; implement role-based access control with roles such as owner, guest, maintenance, and emergency personnel; and enforce session management with automatic logout after 30 minutes of inactivity.
missing_requirements.rationale: Multiple stakeholders require different access levels and secure user management to protect personal data and ensure that only authorized individuals can control critical home functions.

missing_requirements.description: Data encryption, privacy protection, and secure communication requirements are missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall encrypt all personal data at rest and in transit using AES-256 encryption; encrypt all communications using TLS 1.2 or higher; implement data anonymization for usage analytics; and provide user controls for data sharing and deletion in compliance with relevant privacy regulations.
missing_requirements.rationale: The system handles sensitive personal and health data over remote interfaces; strong encryption and privacy controls are essential to safeguard user confidentiality and meet regulatory requirements.

missing_requirements.description: Audit logging of user actions and system events is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall record an immutable, tamper-evident audit log of all user commands, configuration changes, and critical system events with timestamps; store logs securely; and retain them for at least two years.
missing_requirements.rationale: Audit trails are required for security, compliance, and troubleshooting to track system usage and detect unauthorized or erroneous modifications.

missing_requirements.description: System health monitoring, diagnostics, and remote maintenance features are missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall continuously monitor the health status of all connected devices and subsystems; maintain component status logs; provide diagnostic interfaces for troubleshooting; support secure remote diagnostics; deploy firmware and software updates to connected devices; and generate automated alerts for component failures.
missing_requirements.rationale: Comprehensive health monitoring and diagnostic capabilities are critical to detect and resolve failures promptly and to perform remote maintenance in a smart home environment.

missing_requirements.description: System configuration management features are missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall provide centralized configuration management with version control, backup and restore of configuration settings, configuration validation, and rollback capabilities for system settings changes.
missing_requirements.rationale: Robust configuration management is necessary to maintain consistency, support safe updates, and preserve user customizations during system modifications.

missing_requirements.description: Backup management, verification, restoration, and scheduling features are missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall verify backup integrity through automated testing; provide backup restoration capabilities with partial and full restore options; maintain backup logs; periodically test restoration procedures; allow administrators to configure onsite and offsite backup schedules and retention policies; and send alerts on backup failures or retention quota exceedance.
missing_requirements.rationale: Reliable backup and restoration mechanisms, along with scheduling and retention policies, are essential to ensure data recoverability and system continuity.

missing_requirements.description: Network configuration, connectivity, and monitoring features are missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall support Wi-Fi IEEE 802.11 with WPA2/WPA3 security protocols; provide an interface to configure wired and wireless network settings (e.g., SSID, IP settings, DNS, encryption type); support automatic connection, signal strength monitoring, and failover between wired and wireless connections; include network troubleshooting tools, bandwidth monitoring, and automatic network health checks with user notifications for connectivity issues.
missing_requirements.rationale: Comprehensive network configuration and monitoring are necessary to ensure reliable, secure, and diagnosable connectivity in a distributed smart home environment.

missing_requirements.description: Software update and maintenance scheduling requirements are missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall support secure automatic software updates with user approval; schedule maintenance windows; provide update rollback capabilities; minimize service disruption during updates; notify users before and after update completion; and support firmware deployment to connected devices.
missing_requirements.rationale: Regular software and firmware updates are critical to maintain security, add features, and fix bugs, especially for users who may have limited technical support.

missing_requirements.description: Comprehensive accessibility features for older adults are missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall provide voice control integration, high contrast display modes, adjustable audio feedback, large button interfaces, and integrated emergency assistance features to accommodate age-related physical and sensory limitations.
missing_requirements.rationale: Older adults require tailored accessibility features to interact effectively with the smart home system and ensure safety and independence.

missing_requirements.description: Comprehensive emergency response procedures are missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall provide automatic emergency contact notification, integration with emergency services, emergency override controls, and fail-safe modes for critical systems during power outages or communication failures.
missing_requirements.rationale: Robust emergency response capabilities are vital to ensure timely assistance and continuous operation of critical functions in life-threatening situations.

missing_requirements.description: Fail-safe behavior on sensor or actuator malfunction is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall detect failures of critical sensors and actuators (e.g., smoke detectors, garage door motors) and enter predefined safe states (failing closed or open as appropriate), notify users immediately, and log the event in compliance with safety standards such as IEC 61508.
missing_requirements.rationale: Explicit fail-safe behavior is required to maintain safety and regulatory compliance when hardware malfunctions occur.

missing_requirements.description: Carbon monoxide detector entity and requirements are missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall include a CarbonMonoxideDetector entity with attributes for currentLevel, manufacturerThreshold, and userThreshold, and methods to trigger emergency alerts and notify authorities when dangerous CO levels are detected.
missing_requirements.rationale: Carbon monoxide detection is a life-safety critical requirement not represented in the domain model.

missing_requirements.description: Air filter monitoring entity is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall include an AirFilter entity with attributes for filterType, installationDate, currentCondition, and recommendedReplacementDate, and methods to monitor filter condition and track replacement schedules.
missing_requirements.rationale: Requirements specify air filter monitoring and notifications, but no corresponding domain model entity exists.

missing_requirements.description: Pet feeding system entity is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall include a PetFeedingSystem entity with attributes for foodLevel, portionWeight, feedingSchedule, and lastFeedingTime, and methods to dispenseFood, monitorConsumption, and detect RFID for pet identification.
missing_requirements.rationale: Extensive pet feeding functionality is described in requirements but lacks a supporting domain entity.

missing_requirements.description: Food inventory system entity is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall include a FoodInventorySystem entity with attributes for itemName, quantity, expirationDate, rfidTag, and usageHistory, and methods to addItem, removeItem, checkStock, and generateShoppingList.
missing_requirements.rationale: Kitchen inventory management with RFID tracking is detailed in requirements but no domain entity supports it.

missing_requirements.description: Track metadata fields and management are missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall store metadata for each Track, including title, artist, album, duration, genre, bitrate, and fileFormat, and provide methods to updateMetadata and validateAudioFile to support search and categorization.
missing_requirements.rationale: Audio library requirements imply the need for track metadata, but the domain model lacks attributes or methods for tracks.

missing_requirements.description: CRUD operations on heating/cooling zones are missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall allow users to create, rename, and delete Zone instances and assign physical rooms or devices to each zone via the user interface.
missing_requirements.rationale: The domain model defines Zone but requirements only cover temperature settings, not full zone lifecycle management.

missing_requirements.description: Hot tub safe pH and bacterial level threshold configuration is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall allow users to configure safe ranges for pH and bacterial levels in the hot tub, which govern cover operation and chemical administration actions.
missing_requirements.rationale: Cover interlock requirements refer to user-defined norms but the mechanism to set those thresholds is not specified.

missing_requirements.description: Track removal from an existing playlist is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall allow users to remove one or more Track entries from any Playlist.
missing_requirements.rationale: Playlist management must include both addition and removal of tracks to support full edit capabilities.

missing_requirements.description: Historical water filtration data reporting is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall present users with historical reports and charts of daily FiltrationRecord volumes for any user-defined date range, retaining data for at least 90 days.
missing_requirements.rationale: Daily filtration volumes are stored but the ability to review or analyze historical data is not provided.

missing_requirements.description: Historical salt level monitoring reports are missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall record SaltMonitor.currentLevel at least once per day, retain at least 12 months of history, and provide users with historical reports showing salt level trends.
missing_requirements.rationale: Salt level alerts exist but trend analysis and usage forecasting require historical data retention and reporting.

missing_requirements.description: Historical air quality data reporting is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall store AirQualityMonitor.currentQuality readings for at least six months and provide graphical and tabular reports selectable by time period and zone.
missing_requirements.rationale: Air quality alerts are defined but long-term tracking and analysis of air quality is not addressed.

missing_requirements.description: Historical smoke and CO2 detector readings reporting is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall archive readings from SmokeDetector and CarbonDioxideDetector for at least 30 days and enable users to view, filter, and export historical sensor logs.
missing_requirements.rationale: Current requirements define real-time warnings but lack provisions for reviewing past events or levels.

missing_requirements.description: Trigger event logging and query capability is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall log all incoming sensor stimuli as Trigger instances with timestamps and make the event log queryable by users and administrators for diagnostics and automation auditing.
missing_requirements.rationale: A mechanism to record and inspect the full history of sensor triggers is required for troubleshooting and verifying automation behavior.

missing_requirements.description: Pet water bowl automatic refill logic is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall monitor PetWaterBowl.dailyConsumption and water level sensors and automatically open the fill valve when water volume falls below a user-defined threshold.
missing_requirements.rationale: Pet hydration requirements specify providing water but do not define the control mechanism for automatic refilling.

missing_requirements.description: Automatic litter box cleaning cycle initiation is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall initiate the LitterBox cleaning mechanism when odorLevel exceeds the user-defined threshold and disposalUnitFull is false; if disposalUnitFull is true, defer cleaning and notify the user.
missing_requirements.rationale: Notifications for litter box status are specified but the actual activation of the cleaning cycle is not defined.

missing_requirements.description: Recipe metadata fields are not defined
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall store Recipe attributes including name, list of ingredients with quantities, preparation steps, and cook/prep time, and allow users to view and edit these details.
missing_requirements.rationale: Core recipe data fields needed for cooking guidance are omitted from the domain model despite requirements for recipe management.

missing_requirements.description: CRUD operations on user-defined automation routines are missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall allow users to create, modify, and delete automation routines composed of one or more Trigger-Action pairs, with configurable timing and order.
missing_requirements.rationale: Requirements reference automation routines but do not specify how users manage them.

missing_requirements.description: Garage door state query capability is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall allow users to query and display the current status (open, closed, or obstruction detected) of each GarageDoor via any user interface.
missing_requirements.rationale: Users need to know door status before and after remote commands to ensure safe operation.

missing_requirements.description: Energy generation data sampling frequency requirement is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall record EnergyInterface output data at user-configurable intervals, no longer than 15 minutes between samples, to support accurate monitoring and reporting.
missing_requirements.rationale: Monitoring and reporting requirements are defined but the sampling interval for energy data is unspecified.

missing_requirements.description: Automatic switchover to alternative energy sources is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall detect loss of primary electrical supply and automatically switch to available alternative energy sources (e.g., solar, wind) for critical subsystems, and notify users of the power source change.
missing_requirements.rationale: Continuous power for safety and monitoring functions requires automatic source switchover, which is currently unaddressed.

missing_requirements.description: Time synchronization across distributed devices is missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall synchronize clocks on all devices and subsystems to within 100 milliseconds using NTP or an equivalent protocol to ensure accurate timestamping of triggers, records, and logs.
missing_requirements.rationale: Accurate and consistent timekeeping is critical for correlating events and logs in a distributed environment.

domain_model_issues.description: There is no class or package representing UI elements, controls, or consoles needed to satisfy accessibility (REQ-011), button sizing (REQ-012), backlighting (REQ-014), responsive layouts (REQ-016), help function (REQ-019), text-to-speech (REQ-020), and other UI requirements.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce a UserInterface class or subsystem with related UIElement/Button classes, attributes (size, contrast, fontSize), and methods (render(), speakText(), displayHelp()).

domain_model_issues.description: Requirements specify button properties (min size, backlighting), but no Button class exists in the model.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a Button class with attributes size (width, height), backlightEnabled, fontSize, and methods to handle input and styling.

domain_model_issues.description: The model has a Notification class, but no way to capture user preferences (e.g., thresholds, intervals, channels) or relate notifications back to individual users.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Create a NotificationSettings or SubscriberPreferences class linked to User and Notification, storing threshold levels, frequency, and delivery channels.

domain_model_issues.description: Many requirements call for generating reports of various types (radon levels, water usage, airflow, pet consumption, etc.), scheduling and formatting them for user access, but no unified Report class or reporting framework exists.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce a Report class or interface with subclasses (RadonReport, WaterUsageReport, etc.), associations from sensors and record entities, and attributes for report type, data source, format, scheduling, and user access permissions.

domain_model_issues.description: The attribute is a single Double, but requirements call for a mapping of at least four time periods to temperatures (REQ-048).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Change desiredTemperatureSettings to a collection or map (e.g., Map<Period,Double>) and introduce a Period class.

domain_model_issues.description: REQ-044 and REQ-046 require routine recording and retention of radon levels for 90 days, but no RadonRecord or retention mechanism is modeled.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a RadonRecord class with timestamp and level attributes and configure data persistence settings for 90-day retention.

domain_model_issues.description: REQ-229 calls for recording water used and average soil moisture per access point, but the model only has a detector and no record entity.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce a SoilMoistureRecord class linked to IrrigationAccessPoint with timestamp, usedWater, and averageMoisture attributes.

domain_model_issues.description: CoffeeMaker lacks attributes and methods to support filter cleaning notifications (REQ-204), carafe weight detection (REQ-205), emergency stop timing (REQ-207), and shutdown if idle (REQ-208).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Extend CoffeeMaker with attributes filterLevel, carafeWeight, emergencyStopResponseTime, idleTimeout; add methods checkWeight(), triggerBlinkWarning(), and shutOff().

domain_model_issues.description: HotTub misses attributes for pH, bacterial level, waterLevel, safe ranges, and methods to open/close cover based on those thresholds (REQ-210–REQ-223).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes currentPH, bacterialLevel, waterLevel, safePHRange, safeTemperatureRange; implement methods openCover(), closeCover(), soundAlarm(), and recordWaterLevel().

domain_model_issues.description: Requirements for pet feeding (REQ-173–REQ-183) imply a device or subsystem that schedules, portions, and monitors food delivery but no such class exists.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce a PetFoodDelivery class linked to PetWaterBowl and WeightPad with attributes portionWeight, scheduleInterval, and methods dispenseFood(), recordConsumption(), and sendAlert().

domain_model_issues.description: Many requirements reference 'users' and user-specific settings, but there is no User or Occupant class in the domain model to represent people who interact with the system.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a User class with attributes for preferences, authentication credentials, notification settings, and relationships to other entities like rooms, pets, and personal settings.

domain_model_issues.description: Multiple requirements deal with pet management (feeding, health, litter boxes), but there is no Pet class to represent individual pets and their characteristics.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a Pet class with attributes for name, type, weight history, RFID tag, feeding schedule, and health records.

domain_model_issues.description: Many requirements reference rooms and room-specific functionality, but there is no Room class to represent individual rooms and their properties.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a Room class with attributes for name, occupancy status, temperature settings, and relationships to various room-based devices like motion detectors and air flow monitors.

domain_model_issues.description: The System class has too many responsibilities (god object anti-pattern), handling everything from triggers to messages to recipes, violating the single responsibility principle.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Decompose the System class into specialized subsystems like SecuritySystem, MediaSystem, HomeAutomationSystem, etc., each handling related functionality.

domain_model_issues.description: There is no relationship between System and users, even though many requirements specify user interactions and user-specific settings.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add relationships between the System and User classes and between User and subsystems they configure or interact with.

domain_model_issues.description: Requirements mention weather monitoring and forecast retrieval, but there is no representation of weather data or external weather services.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a WeatherService class to handle weather data retrieval and a Weather class to represent current conditions and forecasts.

domain_model_issues.description: The Database class has a configurable transactionRatePerMinute attribute, but REQ-004 specifies a fixed rate of 1000 transactions per minute.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Set a default value of 1000 for transactionRatePerMinute with validation or clarify the requirement specifies a minimum rate instead of a fixed rate.

domain_model_issues.description: Many requirements involve scheduling and time-based operations, but there is no Schedule or Timer class to represent recurring events and time-based triggers.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add Schedule and Timer classes to handle recurring events, time-of-day operations, and scheduled maintenance tasks.

domain_model_issues.description: Requirements for kitchen inventory management (REQ-280–REQ-287) are unmet, as there is no Inventory or FoodItem class in the domain model.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add Inventory and FoodItem classes to handle kitchen stock management, usage tracking, and shopping list generation.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System shall operate on a system capable of multi-processing.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: System shall run on hardware with at least two CPU cores (multi-processing capable) to support concurrent processes, Priority: High; Acceptance Criteria: Verified on target hardware with dual-core CPU under typical load; Dependencies: None; Version: 1.0; Type: Functional; ensuring responsive performance during peak usage.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Original requirement is vague about 'multi-processing' and lacks acceptance criteria, rationale, priority, source, status, dependencies, version and type. Clarifying hardware requirements, adding measurable acceptance criteria and priority improves testability and traceability, and specifying responsive performance ensures clear objectives.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System shall operate on a system capable of near-real time execution of instructions.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: System shall support near-real-time execution with maximum instruction latency of 100 ms, Priority: High; Acceptance Criteria: Measured instruction execution latency <=100 ms under normal load; Dependencies: None; Version: 1.0; Type: Performance.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Specifying a measurable latency threshold and adding priority, acceptance criteria, rationale, and metadata improves clarity, testability, and traceability.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System shall service triggers or stimuli in no more than 500 milliseconds.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: System shall service triggers or stimuli end-to-end within 500 milliseconds under peak load, dependent on REQ-001 and REQ-002 system capabilities, Priority: High; Acceptance Criteria: 95% of triggers serviced within 500 ms during stress tests; Dependencies: REQ-001, REQ-002; Version: 1.0; Type: Performance; ensuring near real-time responsiveness for user safety and satisfaction.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Though timing is specified, the requirement lacked rationale for the 500 ms threshold, quality attribute context, and full dependencies. Adding rationale, priority, measurable acceptance criteria, and identifying dependencies clarifies testability and traceability.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System shall have a database associated with it that can handle transaction processing at a rate of 1000 transactions per minute.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: System shall integrate a database capable of sustaining at least 1000 transactions per minute with <1% error rate under peak load, Priority: Medium; Acceptance Criteria: Database sustains >=1000 TPM with <1% error rate under peak load; Dependencies: REQ-001, REQ-003; Version: 1.0; Type: Performance.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Defining the transaction rate threshold, acceptable error rate, priority, acceptance criteria, and dependencies enhances verifiability and supports proper design sequencing.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System shall have redundant databases for fail over purposes.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: System shall deploy redundant primary and secondary databases configured for automatic failover within 30 seconds, Priority: High; Acceptance Criteria: Failover occurs automatically within 30 seconds of primary database failure; Dependencies: REQ-004; Version: 1.0; Type: Reliability.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Specifying failover timing, priority, acceptance criteria, and dependencies ensures the high availability requirement is measurable and traceable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System shall perform periodical offsite and onsite backups of all configuration and reporting data.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: System shall perform daily onsite backups and weekly offsite backups of all configuration and reporting data, Priority: Medium; Acceptance Criteria: Backups complete successfully as scheduled with verification reports; Dependencies: REQ-005; Version: 1.0; Type: Reliability.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Defining backup frequency, acceptance criteria, and dependencies makes the backup requirement testable and ensures data protection.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System shall support wired Ethernet for 1 gigabit per second, and contain cat 6e cabling.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: System shall support full-duplex 1 Gbps Ethernet over Cat 6e cabling, Priority: Low; Acceptance Criteria: Sustained 1 Gbps throughput measured under load; Dependencies: None; Version: 1.0; Type: Performance.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Specifying full-duplex operation, measurable throughput threshold, priority, acceptance criteria, and metadata clarifies network performance requirements.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System may contain separate SAN device for storage flexibility.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Optional SAN device may be integrated to provide scalable storage capacity, Priority: Low (Optional); Acceptance Criteria: SAN device accessible and configurable via system interface; Dependencies: REQ-004; Version: 1.0; Type: Functional.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Clarifying optionality, priority, acceptance criteria, and dependencies improves planning for future storage expansion.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System may contain separate video recorder/processor for process distribution.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Optional dedicated video recorder/processor may be included to offload video capture tasks, Priority: Low (Optional); Acceptance Criteria: Video capture workload offloaded and processed independently; Dependencies: REQ-004; Version: 1.0; Type: Functional.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Specifying optional status, priority, acceptance criteria, and dependencies ensures clarity for processing load distribution.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: If system supports recording more than three television shows simultaneously, then system shall have separate video recorder.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: If the system records more than three television shows simultaneously, it shall allocate a separate video recorder to maintain performance, Priority: High; Acceptance Criteria: System automatically provisions an additional recorder when more than three concurrent shows are requested; Dependencies: REQ-104; Version: 1.0; Type: Functional.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Adding priority, rationale, acceptance criteria, and dependencies ensures scalability and prevents performance bottlenecks.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System shall be easy to use.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: System shall be easy to use such that 90% of new users can complete basic operations (temperature adjustment, door lock control, camera viewing) within 15 minutes without training, as measured by usability testing.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Original requirement is completely subjective. Adding measurable acceptance criteria (90% success rate, specific tasks, time bound) makes it testable and verifiable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System shall have the option to send notifications to users when water filtration unit needs cleaning.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: System shall provide a user-configurable option to send notifications when the water filtration unit needs cleaning, determined by filter usage exceeding 1000 gallons or 30 days since last cleaning, whichever occurs first.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Original requirement lacks specific criteria for when cleaning is needed. Adding quantitative thresholds makes the requirement testable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System shall not interfere in any way with detector's manufacturer's operating procedures.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: System shall not interfere with smoke and carbon dioxide detectors' manufacturer operating procedures by reading detector signals in read-only mode without modifying configurations or interrupting alarms, ensuring compliance with safety regulations.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Original requirement is vague about 'not interfere.' Specifying read-only operation and no configuration changes provides clear, testable criteria.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System may skip commercials when system is able to detect the commercial.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: System shall provide an optional automatic skipping feature for commercials during playback when commercial segments are detected with at least 90% accuracy using audio/video pattern recognition.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Original requirement uses 'may' and is vague about detection criteria. Changing to 'shall provide optional feature' and specifying accuracy and detection method makes the requirement testable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System shall prevent user from playing back identical media on multiple televisions at the same time.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: System shall prevent concurrent playback of identical media content on multiple televisions to comply with digital rights management requirements, displaying an error message 'Content already playing on [TV location]' when attempted.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Original requirement lacked rationale and user feedback details. Adding DRM rationale and explicit error messaging clarifies intent and testability.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Coffee maker shall stop within 1 microsecond when button is pressed.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Coffee maker shall stop within 1 microsecond when the emergency stop button is pressed to ensure immediate cessation of operation for user safety.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Requirement is specific in timing but lacks rationale. Adding safety context clarifies the necessity of the precise timing.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System shall allow users to enter food associated with RFID tag into the kitchen inventory system.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: System shall allow users to enter food items into the kitchen inventory system by scanning RFID tags, associating each tag with item name, quantity, expiration date, and purchase date through a data-validated interface.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Original requirement lacked detail on data fields and validation. Defining specific fields and validation makes it testable and user-friendly.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: System shall record messages for recipients along with date, time stamp, and incoming phone number to non-volatile memory.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: System shall record voice messages for recipients to non-volatile memory with metadata including date (YYYY-MM-DD), time stamp (HH:MM:SS), and incoming phone number (when available), supporting storage capacity for at least 100 messages per mailbox.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Original requirement lacked format and capacity details. Adding metadata formats and storage limits improves testability and ensures compliance with storage requirements.

reasoning.domain_model: Combined broad subsystem classes from Model1 with additional content classes from Model2. Retained detailed attributes and methods from Model1 for core devices, enriched the VideoMetadata and Zone classes with Model2 fields, and integrated new classes (Track, Message, Recipe) and Playlist-Track relationship. Consolidated Database methods, preserved Backup processes, and maintained consistent aggregation, composition, and association relationships. Conflicts such as overlapping pet and audio concepts were resolved by centralizing audio tracks under Track and recording messages via Message. The result is a unified domain model capturing both operational behaviors and metadata.
reasoning.analysis:
Analysis aggregated using openai with specialized component processing:
- requirement_completeness: Combined assessments from two LLMs by matching each requirement ID, selecting the lower completeness score where scores differed (they were identical), merging all missing_elements arrays to include every distinct missing attribute, and preserving comprehensive suggested improvements and rationales from both analyses. This conservative consolidation ensures no insight is lost while maintaining clarity and traceability.
- requirement_issues: Merged issues by mapping source issue types to the four allowed categories (Ambiguity→Incomplete, Missing Context/Testability→Missing, Conflict→Conflict, Implementation→Inconsistency), preserved all unique findings, unified duplicates (e.g., REQ-017 Ambiguity/Testability), retained original severities, combined detailed descriptions and fixes, and ensured consistent structure.
- missing_requirements: Both provided analyses contained the same set of 32 missing requirements. We merged them into a single list without duplication, preserving all unique requirements and using the most detailed descriptions, categories, severities, suggested requirements, affected model elements, and rationales.
- domain_model_issues: We consolidated issues from both analyses, preserving all unique entries and merging the duplicate Report entry into a single comprehensive issue with combined descriptions, suggestions, and aggregated affected requirements. We mapped Claude’s 'Incorrect' issue type to 'Inconsistent' to comply with allowed values. Each issue retains the most detailed information from both sources, ensuring clear identification of domain model problems and actionable fixes.
